snippet.textDisplay:
We can kiss by by to the league if we do not bring in a striker this window who can play in our system against physical teams. We seem to be a one man team (Buff) and look toothless without him. Irreplaceable unless we spend monopoly money which is never going to happen anytime soon. Unfortunately we are a team with no winning mentality (being able to control the adrenaline whether excited or nervous to play your normal game) yet.

The only positive for me was the impact Polster made and changed the whole dynamic of the right side for us. Perhaps if he had been on from the start things would have been different. Yet again when called upon he never put a foot wrong. Feed up with our boo boys slagging yet another one of our players (just not good enough bollocks).

Need to stop going to warm training camps in the winter break it just seems to declimatise us and we so far just have not been up to speed when we come back both years.

snippet.textDisplay: The only positive I could see today was Polsters performance since coming on. Too many players weren’t at it and I never feel confident having Defoe on his own up front. The ball never sticks to him, he’s easily out-muscled and he doesn’t have the pace to get in behind. If we can’t get a ball into his feet inside the box he never looks like scoring and can’t create opportunities for himself like Morelos. We need a striker. Nevertheless, I don’t even think that would’ve won us the game today since Kamara, Flanagan, Katic and Davis were so poor. Not enough fight today.
